{"key":"post-6515580","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6515580</id>\n<content>Don't use the oven.  Air is a poor conductor of heat, so the the material on the edges of your bag will be overcooked while the middle is still cool.  It's best to pasteurize straw in a bath so the hot water is around each and every piece, not trying to heat from the edges toward the middle.  Remember, straw is an insulator.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>6515615</next>\n<prev>6515114</prev>\n<first>6515105</first>\n<last>6516185</last>\n<when>1170259590</when>\n<utime>01/31/07 06:06 PM</utime>\n</post>"}